cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper deals with interpretation methods for neural models in natural language processing (NLP), which suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the limitations of existing interpretation methods and proposes a fine-tuning approach, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper's discussion of adversarial examples and confidence calibration suggests a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions heatmap visualization, which is a common technique in computer vision, indicating a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper's focus on neural models and their behaviors suggests a connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
